The Commission shall have the exclusive right to use the name United States Boxing Commission. Any person who, without the permission of the Commission, uses that name or any other exclusive name, trademark, emblem, symbol, or insignia of the Commission for the purpose of inducing the sale or exchange of any goods or services, or to promote any exhibition, performance, or sporting event, shall be subject to suit in a civil action by the Commission for the remedies provided in the Act of July 5, 1946 (commonly known as the 

                    Trademark Act of 1946
                  ; 
                    15 U.S.C. 1051 et seq.
                  ).

